c is highly complex and artful, not only having immediate emotional impact but also comprising some of the most outstanding music produced in the twentieth century.Bringing together some of the most influential international scholars on the subject, this anthology provides a detailed, diverse and accessible perspective on music in the cinema. As well as chapters on the techniques and views of film music and on film music scholarship, the book embraces topics as diverse as Bernard Herrmann's music for Welles's Citizen Kane, the use of discs to accompany silent films and gender and the cinematic soundscape.Key FeaturesAn original collection of essays on film music in the twentieth centuryThe Introduction provides a historical perspective on the art of film musicBrings together a wide range of approaches to film music  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Mrz 2022) 0aMotion picture musicxHistory and criticism. 4aFilm, Media & Cultural Studies. 7aPERFORMING ARTS / Film & Video / History & Criticism.2bisacsh1 aAllen, Michael, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBuhler, James, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCochran, Alfred W., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDonnelly, K. J., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFlinn, Caryl, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFranklin, Peter, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGarner, Ken, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNeumeyer, David, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRosar, William H., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aStilwell, Robynn J., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators